<Author>girafferama
<Content>Good basic hotel This hotel is great if you want a basic place to stop whilst sightseeing in Barcelona. We stayed for two nights. It is a five minute walk from Maria Cristina tube stop, which is easily accessible from the airport or train station. It is in a slightly residential area with a supermarket, cafe and bank 2 mins away on foot. It is easy to find (the hotel offered directions), although we did arrive late and got lost in the dark when we walked down the wrong street!The room was fairly basic but very clean and had air conditioning. The bathroom was very nice with a good selection of complimentary toiletries and the room was cleaned for us after our first night. The staff were friendly and helpful. The Camp Nou stadium is literally a 5 minute walk away, so very well located if you are looking to visit, from there we were able to pick up the tourist bus to do our sightseeing and got the tube back quite late in the evening with out any problems. Only complaint would be that the walls appear to be very thin, so you can hear people in adjacent rooms, but this didn't really cause us any problems.All in all a great place to stay if you want somewhere cheap and easy. 
