<Content>It is noisy, at least in level 2 .... Ask for upper floors Yes, the hotel is easy to reach by underground, is comparably cheap for Barcelona, is clean, has good breakfast. You can ask for the key to the safe deposit box for a deposit (it is free). The single rooms are tiny but OK just to stay the night (nothing more). And on the way to the subway tehre is a a corte ingles mid-size city grocery open almost 24X7 - great to by snacks, bottle of drinks and the like avoiding tourist prices elsewhere .... BUT: I had a room right in level 2 above reception and kittchen. I woke up every day when the kittchen started about 30 minutes before breakast start, maybe because they spoke so loud with the front desk. Also, shower of next room and people walking above were as load as if you were in there room. It is one of these congrete buildings where the inner walls carry the weight and usually transmit noise easily. Believe me, I have read a lot of reviews about hotels with noise complaints that I considered OK, but this room in perticular was sound-open ... Do not get me wrong: Without the front desk /kittchen noise it may very well be quiet, SO DO ASK FOR A ROOM IN THE UPPER FLOORS, the hotels has quiete a few floors. 
