<Content>Very noisy, Tiny room, treated rudely Very noisy, Tiny room, Rude deskman Review: I remained only 3 of my planned 12 day stay in this hotel due to the fact that I just couldn't sleep. I could hear toilets flushing, showers being taken, doors banging. My first night there, it became so hot in the tiny room, I called the desk to ask how to regulate the heat. I was told that it was winter in Barcelona and I couldn't regulate the heat at all and to open my window. I did. At 3:30 AM people were still outside talking and walking by. I closed the window. I found where there was a knob on the radiator which I turned completely off. It remained in this position until just before I checked out. On morning number 1 and with permission of the guy behind the desk, I was allowed to take my breakfast tray up to my room due to smoking in the small eating room. On morning #3 I was promptly scolded in Spanish by the female dining room worker because I was taking a yogurt up to my room. I felt quite humiliated. When I had to check out because I became ill, the desk clerk was rude. He kept telling me that I was to stay 12 nights. Twice I repeated: I know, but I'm sick and must go home. He stated that instead of the discounted rate I had been given, I would have to pay the full rate of 5 more Euros. I gladly paid it and got the heck out of there. The room walls are paper thin and you can hear everything. If they truly redid this hotel 4 years ago, they really need to add insulation between the walls. I think I read somewhere that this hotel was a converted college dorm. Although clean, I wouldn't recommend this hotel to anyone unless you can sleep though anything. 
