<Content>A very good two star hotel I had a good experience in this hotel. It is two stars so no luxury, but they get the basics right: tidy room, clean sheets, decent size and equipped bathroom, TV, work desk and air conditioned facilities. The breakfest is basic - cold cuts only - but appropriate. The hotel is 5-10 minutes walking from the Maria Christina metro stop, in the business district of Barcelona. Very nice shopping opportunities all around. It took me 30 minutes to get to the hotel from the airport using public transportation (train from airport to Station Sants and then green metro line to Maria Christina station). Paid EUR 48 per night. 
